  "time_ut": 1656994590,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0db1\u0dba - \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0ddc\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dad\u0dbb \u0db1\u0dc0  \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A new office transport train service between Jaffna and Kilinochchi",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In view of the fuel crisis in the country, steps will be taken to start the new train service between Kilinochchi and Jaffna from the coming week to prevent the inconvenience caused by the lack of buses for the transportation of office workers, says Mr. Douglas Devananda.",
        "Every day, thousands of public and private sector employees come to Kilinochchi from Jaffna and according to the request made by the Minister from the Ministry of Transport to start this train service for their convenience, a group of officials from the Ministry of Transport came to Kilinochchi and after investigating the matter, the Ministry of Transport decided to start the train transport from the coming week. The officials informed Fisheries Minister Douglas Devananda that Minister Bandula Gunawardena had given instructions.",
        "Officials of the Ministry of Transport and General Manager of Railways A.D.P. Mr. Seneviratne, Jaffna Station Master Pradeepan, Kilinochchi District Station Master Shri Mohan, Fisheries Minister's Additional Coordinating Secretary Kotiswaran Rushankan have discussed the matters required to start the new train service.",
        "Afterwards, a special discussion was held with the Northern Province Railway Service Director Visumidara and Kilinochchi Station Master Sigamani, District Secretary Mrs. Rupavathi Ketheeswaram and the team and discussed at length the issues related to starting the train service. Speaking in this discussion, the Deputy General Manager of Railways said that according to the request of the Minister of Fisheries Douglas Devananda, steps will be taken to start this train service within the coming week and the start date will be announced soon."
      ],
